						               													<description>The map shows there's an old ruined temple out here somewhere. Sure to be loaded with treasure and if nobody else has looted it yet, it can't be too heavily guarded. Right?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Sunken Temple is the first Scenario for Five Leagues From the Borderlands 2, allowing you to go treasure hunting in an old temple ruin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Of course, first you need to find the place and deal with bandits, wolves and the cursed remnants of the temple itself.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Instead of providing you with new encounter tables, this Scenario plays out more like a role playing adventure, as you move from stage to stage.&amp;#10;Consisting of a few encounters with  dice challenges in between, the Scenario should give you an entertaining long afternoon or a few evenings, depending on pacing.&amp;#10;Ideally suited for a relatively inexperienced war band, there's something here for everyone with some sweet loot at the end.&amp;#10;You also get a chance to pick up a new NPC with a useful quirk of their own.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note that this is an expansion for the Five Leagues miniatures rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The scenario is written for the second edition rules, though first edition players should be able to use it without too much trouble.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is NOT a stand alone game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
